nt|^b@2^z@3|cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|But I love to make aggressive preempts in 3rd seat. Here is a good rule to follow when opening in 3rd seat. It turns out, after 2 passes, on average, the 2 passed hands hold 16 HCP which means that 3rd seat and 4th seat hold 24 HCP between them on average.|
PG| ***** 103 ***** |


nt|^b@2^z@3|cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If you subtract your HCP in 3rd seat from 24, you know approximately how many HCP 4th. seat is likely to have. Here assuming East is going to pass, I would subtract my 6 HCP from 24 and figure that West has about 18 HCP on average.|
PG| ***** 104 ***** |


nt|^b@2^z@3|cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So I would want to make it as difficult as possible for the opponents. Therefore, despite only having five so-so hearts I would open a weak 2@H bid in 3rd. seat.|MB|2H|
